body_html:
You are compiling TensorFlow 1.6? or do you really mean Python 1.6? If the latter, we do not support less like python 2.x.

As far as I can tell, the underlying tensor implementation must be able to fit in the kMaxEagerParentSize. So in principal it can be increased with impunity. Somehow in your compile the base class tensor size is larger (probably alignment differences between compilers?)

@alextp, do you have any insights?
